##Wuhan "four categories of personnel" centralized treatment of the first day: "WE ARE NOT ABANDONED! "

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

In the eyes of medical experts, mass internment and isolation are the first step. Next, the diagnosis, classification, treatment and admission of suspected patients will be a comprehensive test of the ability of multi-resource allocation such as medical treatment, material and personnel allocation

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wen | CAIJING reporters Li Shiyun, Gao Honghao, Fanggongyiliu CAIJING special correspondent Wuhan Xinna, Liu Yiqin Intern Ma Kexin

Editor | Song Wei

At 9:30 am on February 3,2020, Chen Wei received a text message from the Wuhan Union Hospital: "You tested for COVID-19 pneumonia nucleic acid on January 29. The results are as follows: Shuangyang District (confirmed) . "

Most people would have been devastated by this text. That is not bad news for the "suspected patients" in Wuhan, where a diagnosis means a hospital stay. They no longer have to drag their tired bodies to and from the hospital for injections, no longer have to wait in line at the appointed hospital in the early hours of the morning to get the nucleic acid test paper.

On February 2, the Wuhan Municipal Government and the Health Commission took a series of new measures to ease the difficulty of identifying suspected patients. "CAIJING" reporters learned that on February 2, Wuhan added a number of nucleic acid reagent testing institutions, respectively, Wuhan University People's Hospital, Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, Puai Hospital and so on.

Also on February 2, Wuhan decided to requisition 17 fourth-batch and 10 fifth-batch designated hospitals with a total of 2,183 beds. On that day, Huoshenshan hospital was built and delivered more than 1,000 beds. Three new "shelter hospitals" , with 3,400 beds, were opened Wednesday at the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center, the Wembley Arena and the living room of Wuhan, mainly for newly diagnosed patients with mild cases of pneumonia.

At this point, the shortage of beds in Wuhan will be eased.

On February 2, the Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued the tenth circular, decided from the date of issuance of the circular, "four categories of personnel" centralized treatment and isolation.

The "four categories" are: confirmed patients with new crown pneumonia, suspected patients with new crown pneumonia, patients with fever who can not definitively rule out the possibility of new crown pneumonia, confirmed patients in close contact. Among them, confirmed patients with severe illness must be sent to designated hospitals, suspected patients with severe illness must be admitted to hospitals for treatment, confirmed patients who can not enter designated hospitals, suspected patients who can not be admitted to hospitals for isolation, need to commandeer other hospitals or hotels, such as centralized isolation treatment.

The contents of the above-mentioned circular have been generally affirmed by all parties. A medical worker told CAIJING: "This is a very important measure. Wuhan has finally done it. LET'S IMPLEMENT IT! "

At the same time, the highly concerned outside Wuhan Huoshenshan hospital has been officially opened. The first 50 patients were admitted on the morning of Feb. 4, and many saw them as a hope for treatment, CCTV reported. A medical staff told the "CAIJING" reporter, mild or with the main community home quarantine, Huoshenshan and other hospitals will address the needs of some seriously ill patients.

On Feb. 3, the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Prevention and control headquarters said it was tracking requests for help from friends and relatives posted on various Internet platforms. It has so far followed up on 135 requests, saying, "the patients have been properly settled. "

In the opinion of the medical experts interviewed by Caijing, the first step is to centralize detention and isolation. Next, the diagnosis and treatment of suspected patients should be classified, it will be a comprehensive test of the ability of multiple resource allocation such as medical treatment, material and personnel allocation. We believe that all parties concerned can work together to tide over the difficulties.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(click to view larger image)

ISOLATION POINT: receiving heavy duty, not enough preparation

A nurse explained that the hotel is only observation quarantine point, can not injection can not take medicine, can not arrange hospitalization.

On the morning of February 2, the Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued a notice, decided to confirm, suspected and other "four categories of personnel" concentrated treatment and isolation. "We were not abandoned! " One patient recalled to a reporter from Caijing how he felt when he saw the notice.

On the morning of February 3, Wang Sen, a resident of a residential community in Wuhan Qiao Estuary, received a phone call from the community, informing her to quarantine the hotel. A week ago, she had a low-grade fever with a temperature of around 37.5 C, making her the focus of a suspected case of new coronary pneumonia in the community.

By the time Wang Sen arrived, the hotel rooms in the quarantined hotel were nearly full. Wang Sen was 48th, with staff saying there were 28 rooms left. In the next 15 minutes, three police cars arrived at the hotel with fever patients from the community. They were told there were no rooms and left in a hurry.

The note at the hotel's entrance reads as if it were a "new pneumonia quarantine" , with about 140 febrile patients, each with a room. Most checked in with at least two bags, some with pots, and looked hopeful.

CAIJING reporter learned that Wuhan recently opened a number of new isolation points in the past two days, some are only responsible for isolation, not all of the hospital interface.

In two or three days, people who live here will be tested for nucleic acid kits, a paramedic on the scene said. Those who come back negative can just walk away. Patients with mild illnesses will continue to be quarantined in hotels and those with severe illnesses will need to go to a hospital.

At 5:00 p.m. on February 2, The stone in Luo Yi's heart finally fell to the ground. His brother, who had been seriously ill for several days and had no access to medical care, was informed by the community health station that he could move into the central isolation point that night.

At 8 p.m. , Ms. Luo received a call from the driver of the Community Health Station: "your brother needs to leave the segregated hotel. " He was stunned. Then the brother, who had a fever of over 39 degrees, was sent home. The Community Health Station advised the family that the fever was serious, and that the isolation point had no doctors and no testing equipment, so it was better to stay at home.

Luo Yi's older brother was taken back to the car, sent to the First Hospital in Wuhan, queuing for a new round of tests, and finally returned to their homes.

For the isolation point did not arrange the corresponding isolation measures, Luo Yi felt a little regret.

According to the "technical guidelines for centralized observation of patients with community fever" issued on February 2, in principle each observation point should be provided with 1 doctor (preferably a general practitioner or a suction doctor) for every 50 persons, so as to be able to take over shifts. In case of aggravation of the fever, the case should be reported to the local Township Health Center or Community Health Service Center immediately and sent to the designated medical institutions for isolation treatment, sampling and testing.

A staff member of the district government's general duty office explained to the Caijing reporter that during the implementation of the quarantine point, medical staff needed to draw from the front line, patients needed to live, eat and sleep, and various conditions needed to be worked out one by one.

"It was very difficult to do these things with the city closed, so it was a gradual process, " he said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Detection Reagent: Some sensitivity is not high, need to repeat detection

"If it's positive, it's positive, but if it's negative, it's not necessarily negative, " the doctor said.

Neither the isolation points nor the community triage arrangements can get around the fact that most hospitals require patients to be admitted with a confirmed diagnosis, and current procedures require that the critical point of diagnosis be the test capacity of the kit.

A good trend is that the production capacity of nucleic acid confirmatory reagents is opening up, more and more suspected patients can use as soon as possible. The isolation points in the different districts of Wuhan have also become a new way for many suspected patients to obtain test strips.

According to the CAIJING reporter, the following new hospitals are being opened in Wuhan for NUCLEIC ACID TESTING:

People's Hospital of Wuhan University, but only if there are test certificates from other hospitals; Pu Ai Hospital, which can be done in both hospital areas, needs symptoms and CT, and needs to go to the fever clinic first; Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, needs to make an appointment in advance, after the appointment is made, you can make an appointment for five days. At present, it is free. At Zhongshan Hospital, you can make an appointment for more than 100 cases a day. The hospital is accompanied by a medical guide. At Tongji Hospital, the result will be available in two days at a cost of 300 yuan. At Wuhan Zhongshan Hospital, need to take the medical records directly to the hospital to find a fever clinic billing test, no appointment, recommended to go in the morning.

Li Lanjuan, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and a member of the National Health Commission's High Level Expert Group, said in a media interview on Feb. 3 that Wuhan currently does not have enough reagents to test, so not everyone can get tested. "early detection, early diagnosis, early isolation and early treatment can not be achieved in Wuhan at present. We hope the whole country will support Wuhan. "

CAIJING reporters also learned that in some hospitals in Wuhan, the relevant test appointment queue and test cycle is still too long, some institutions detected a high rate of "false negative" , some patients need repeated testing.

Shen Jun, Assistant Director of the Emergency Center and Director of Emergency Surgery at Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University, told Caijing that in the early stages of NCP, due to the uncertainty of some test kits, sometimes asymptomatic patients also test positive for nucleic acid, and hospitals do "Shuangyang District tests" to reconfirm. But he believes it is no longer necessary.

"We now know that nucleic acid reagents are very specific, but not very sensitive, which means if you test positive, you're positive, but if you test negative, you're not necessarily negative, " he said.

If the patient's first test is negative, that means the doctor may have to do it again.

A doctor at a designated hospital in Wuhan told Caijing that he had seen patients with severe viral pneumonia on a CT scan of the lungs, both negative for nucleic acid and eventually positive. The positive rate of nucleic acid reagent in their hospital was 45% .

Before in the mouth of a number of suspected patients, the row on the test kit comparable to the "lottery. ". The test kit is not 100% accurate, the need to repeat the test, will extend the patient's waiting time in hospital. This also resulted in a high-risk patient with a ground-glass CT of the lung, who was denied a bed because the reagent test came back negative.

Shen Jun's colleague, Zhang Xiaochunfa, director of the imaging department at Zhongnan Hospital, posted a friend's note suggesting CT imaging as the primary basis for new pneumonia. She has seen patients with occult onset, one or even multiple negative nucleic acid, without any clinical symptoms, resulting in family clustering. Zhang recommended mandatory isolation in hotels or elsewhere for all patients with positive CT findings.

It is reported that Zhang Xiaochun's family also has the infection, she said a doctor family protection measures to be stricter than ordinary citizens, not to mention ordinary citizens.

Another medical expert told Caijing that even though the document has made provision, today's cases of infection may not be completely resettled for a while, and it will take time to strengthen home protection.

Bed: Vulcan Mountain and the Shelter Hospital are being treated

"after all, everything is getting better, and I hope it gets better. "

In Wuhan, where medical resources are tight, beds are reserved primarily for patients who have been diagnosed with, or are suspected of, new coronary pneumonia.

Having a bed means having a professional medical staff, professional medical equipment support, when patients appear suddenly, dangerous situation, can be timely treatment. That's why many patients who are getting sicker are desperate for a bed.

Wuhan is scrambling to add hospital beds that can accommodate the most severely ill. By 23:00 on February 3, the city's designated hospitals in Wuhan had used 8,279 beds, larger than the open beds of 8,199. The Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission said that some hospitals had tried their best to arrange extra beds in accordance with the requirement of "receiving as much as possible. ". Beds remain an important issue for Wuhan to grapple with.

February 4,10:00 am, Wembley Arena. "CAIJING" reporters saw wearing the uniform of the city administration into the beginning of the closure of the museum. After that, there will be 90 medical staff in charge of the daily monitoring and treatment of patients in the hospital, "the medical staff in place, began to treat patients. "

A quilt folded in two, a pad on the bed board, a cover on the body, under the electric blanket. Next to the single bed is a set of desks and chairs for personal use. The medical team that comes to support has central South Hospital, Volunteer Team Has Xiang Ya Hospital.

The night of Feb. 3 was a sleepless night for field workers. A construction worker said he only slept for 50 minutes. "then he woke up and was afraid to answer the phone. He sat up and ran to the scene for fear of what might happen. "

On the morning of February 4th, they were busy moving plates, separating the different areas into separate, disconnected spaces. Medical staff work area and patient area are separate, they have their own living area, can toilet, wash.

Several staff members also posted signs above the stadium's passageway, "unit two. ". The person in charge of the site, each unit, representing a sick area, the gymnasium will have three sick areas. Doctors and patients also have separate pathways that allow for effective physical isolation.

"It was done by hand overnight, " said a person in charge, laying out community drawings on the spot. "there was no time to make drawings with a computer. " According to a reporter from Caijing, the designer of the Linjian hospital designed the Zhongnan Building, same as Mount Thor. CAIJING reporter learned that the site also needs to open a new fever clinic, renovation is expected to be completed by 12 pm on the 4th.

On the other side of the city, Wuhan's Huoshenshan hospital has been completed and put into service, starting Feb. 4, to concentrate on patients with COVID-19 pneumonia. The hospital has a total Gross leasable area of 33,900 square meters, with 1,000 beds, and has set up intensive care units, critical care units and general ward units, as well as auxiliary departments for infection control, examination, special diagnosis and radiological diagnosis.

There are 2,600 beds at Vulcan Mountain and Thor Mountain hospitals. Some people are worried about whether there are enough beds? A doctor at a designated hospital told Caijing that at present, the number of patients with serious illness is not very large, most of them are patients with mild illness, can be isolated at home, or the community unified arrangements for isolation.

A doctor at a designated front-line hospital told the CAIJING reporter that the opening of the Vulcan Mountain and Raytheon Mountain hospitals can effectively ease the pressure on hospitals in urban areas, and patients with severe diagnoses can be immediately transferred to hospitals, "We can open up beds for other patients. "

"after all, everything is getting better and better, so I hope it will get better and better, " said Li Li, who was interviewed by Caijing reporter before.

(Wang Sen, Luo Yi, Liu Mei and Li Li Li are pseudonyms)
